  "id": "BIT-discourse-2025-64528",
  "summary": "Users are able to find users by name even when `enable_names` is off",
  "details": "Discourse is an open source discussion platform. Prior to versions 3.5.3, 2025.11.1, and 2025.12.0, an attacker who knows part of a username can find the user and their full name via UI or API, even when `enable_names` is disabled. Versions 3.5.3, 2025.11.1, and 2025.12.0 contain a fix.",
